1
00:01:36,439 --> 00:01:39,400
Old Tong, I really didn't see it coming.

2
00:01:40,000 --> 00:01:41,480
You're quite the operator.

3
00:01:43,159 --> 00:01:45,000
You got Director Qiu on your side.

4
00:01:45,159 --> 00:01:46,879
And you've got a big shot backing you.

5
00:01:47,400 --> 00:01:48,959
A true master stays hidden.

6
00:01:49,319 --> 00:01:50,719
Manager Liu, I really don't.

7
00:01:50,719 --> 00:01:51,920
I know.

8
00:01:52,560 --> 00:01:54,599
You and Xiao Jia have never quite gotten along.

9
00:01:55,159 --> 00:01:56,680
I've already made arrangements for you.

10
00:01:56,719 --> 00:01:58,319
No, no, I really don't mean anything by it.

11
00:01:58,319 --> 00:01:59,760
I get it, I get it.

12
00:01:59,760 --> 00:02:01,760
It has nothing to do with you, don't worry.

13
00:02:01,760 --> 00:02:03,079
I really don't mean that.

14
00:02:12,680 --> 00:02:14,280
Given that Comrade Jia Zhilong

15
00:02:14,479 --> 00:02:16,039
has had poor performance recently,

16
00:02:16,319 --> 00:02:17,639
it has been decided after discussion

17
00:02:17,800 --> 00:02:19,439
to adjust his position.

18
00:02:19,879 --> 00:02:21,039
Comrade Tong Qiu,

19
00:02:21,319 --> 00:02:23,280
has shown outstanding performance and a serious attitude.

20
00:02:23,560 --> 00:02:25,759
After collective deliberation by management,

21
00:02:25,800 --> 00:02:28,039
it is proposed to appoint him as Assistant Branch Manager.

22
00:02:28,719 --> 00:02:30,280
This has been reported to the relevant authorities.

23
00:02:32,520 --> 00:02:34,360
Good. Meeting adjourned.

24
00:02:37,319 --> 00:02:38,120
Well, well.

25
00:02:38,120 --> 00:02:38,599
Congratulations.

26
00:02:38,599 --> 00:02:39,719
Congratulations!

27
00:02:40,120 --> 00:02:41,960
You went straight for the big move.

28
00:02:41,960 --> 00:02:42,280
Old Tong.

29
00:02:42,280 --> 00:02:44,639
I always said you'd make something of yourself.

30
00:02:44,639 --> 00:02:45,000
Brother Tong.

31
00:02:45,000 --> 00:02:45,479
I told you so.

32
00:02:45,479 --> 00:02:46,759
Our Brother Tong was bound to get promoted.

33
00:02:46,759 --> 00:02:47,360
Exactly.

34
00:02:47,360 --> 00:02:48,120
You're treating us to a meal!

35
00:02:48,120 --> 00:02:48,759
You're buying dinner!

36
00:02:48,759 --> 00:02:50,240
You absolutely have to treat us tonight!

37
00:02:57,800 --> 00:02:59,479
No, no, no, Manager Jia.

38
00:03:01,360 --> 00:03:02,439
Why are you so upset?

39
00:03:02,439 --> 00:03:03,960
Alright, alright, just ignore him.

40
00:03:04,479 --> 00:03:05,719
Where are we eating tonight?

41
00:03:05,719 --> 00:03:06,639
Barbecue.

42
00:03:07,520 --> 00:03:08,280
No, it's not that.

43
00:03:08,280 --> 00:03:10,800
This is just the leadership showing me favor.

44
00:03:10,800 --> 00:03:11,280
The leaders appreciate me.

45
00:03:11,280 --> 00:03:11,960
What are you being modest for?

46
00:03:11,960 --> 00:03:14,280
I'm not being modest, not at all.

47
00:03:14,280 --> 00:03:15,080
Not being low-key either.

48
00:03:15,080 --> 00:03:15,840
Okay, okay.

49
00:03:15,840 --> 00:03:17,319
We'll... we'll do it later, later.

50
00:03:18,240 --> 00:03:20,000
I'll treat everyone later, I promise.

51
00:03:20,000 --> 00:03:20,879
No, no, we're treating you.

52
00:03:20,879 --> 00:03:22,479
No, no, no, it's on me, on me.

53
00:03:22,560 --> 00:03:23,520
I'm heading out first.

54
00:03:24,599 --> 00:03:25,800
How come he's all flustered

55
00:03:25,800 --> 00:03:27,439
after getting a promotion?

56
00:03:27,439 --> 00:03:27,800
Let's go.

57
00:03:27,800 --> 00:03:29,039
He's just dizzy with excitement.

58
00:03:29,039 --> 00:03:29,520
Let's go, let's go.

59
00:03:29,520 --> 00:03:30,840
We're out of here too, let's go.

60
00:03:30,840 --> 00:03:31,520
Let's go.

61
00:03:36,599 --> 00:03:37,520
Honey.

62
00:03:39,240 --> 00:03:40,560
Listen to this.

63
00:03:42,280 --> 00:03:43,879
Something huge happened to me today.

64
00:03:44,120 --> 00:03:46,919
Don't rush, don't rush. Take your time.

65
00:03:48,400 --> 00:03:49,599
Just now.

66
00:03:50,759 --> 00:03:51,759
Just now.

67
00:03:53,280 --> 00:03:55,800
I'm getting promoted. Assistant Branch Manager.

68
00:03:55,879 --> 00:03:57,199
You scared me.

69
00:03:57,199 --> 00:03:59,120
I thought something bad happened to you.

70
00:03:59,120 --> 00:04:00,120
No, no, no.

71
00:04:00,120 --> 00:04:00,840
It's just that I feel...

72
00:04:01,560 --> 00:04:03,120
The more I think about it, the more nervous I get.

73
00:04:03,120 --> 00:04:04,319
What are you nervous about?

74
00:04:04,879 --> 00:04:06,560
You've been hoping for this for so long.

75
00:04:07,000 --> 00:04:08,120
Don't you worry.

76
00:04:08,120 --> 00:04:09,360
You earned this all by yourself.

77
00:04:09,360 --> 00:04:11,000
No, no, no, that's not it.

78
00:04:11,120 --> 00:04:12,039
Look.

79
00:04:12,039 --> 00:04:13,759
I finally figured it out now.

80
00:04:13,879 --> 00:04:15,560
If I just rise up like this,

81
00:04:15,599 --> 00:04:17,639
how many eyes will be watching me?

82
00:04:17,639 --> 00:04:19,279
Take Xiao Jia, for example.

83
00:04:19,560 --> 00:04:20,879
He was originally the Assistant Branch Manager.

84
00:04:20,879 --> 00:04:22,920
By convention, after a full year he'd be promoted to Vice President.

85
00:04:22,920 --> 00:04:25,120
Now that I'm going up, he's going down.

86
00:04:25,279 --> 00:04:27,639
You have no idea how he was glaring at me.

87
00:04:27,639 --> 00:04:28,920
Alright, alright.

88
00:04:29,040 --> 00:04:30,600
Don't overthink it.

89
00:04:31,160 --> 00:04:32,959
If you're afraid of this and afraid of that,

90
00:04:33,120 --> 00:04:34,680
you might as well not go to work at all.

91
00:04:36,800 --> 00:04:39,000
Husband, you do your job well.

92
00:04:39,519 --> 00:04:40,839
No one's going to do anything to you.

93
00:04:41,000 --> 00:04:42,360
Trust me, okay?

94
00:04:43,399 --> 00:04:46,319
Right? Yeah, you're right.

95
00:04:46,519 --> 00:04:49,120
Well, then we'll just take it one step at a time.

96
00:04:49,120 --> 00:04:49,800
Right?

97
00:04:51,079 --> 00:04:52,800
Okay, I'll get back to work then.

98
00:04:53,720 --> 00:04:54,959
Bye, sweetie.

99
00:04:55,120 --> 00:04:56,120
Love you.

100
00:05:04,079 --> 00:05:04,800
Yeah.

101
00:05:06,519 --> 00:05:07,279
Yeah.

102
00:05:13,839 --> 00:05:15,000
Time to get off work.

103
00:05:30,199 --> 00:05:31,600
He really got promoted.

104
00:05:32,199 --> 00:05:33,000
Promoted.

105
00:05:34,920 --> 00:05:38,000
You're not lying to us this time, are you?

106
00:05:38,079 --> 00:05:39,519
I'm really not lying to you.

107
00:05:40,360 --> 00:05:41,600
Great! That's great!

108
00:05:41,600 --> 00:05:43,439
Good son. You've made something of yourself.

109
00:05:44,360 --> 00:05:45,639
So, with this promotion...

110
00:05:45,800 --> 00:05:47,519
...your salary should go up a bit, right?

111
00:05:47,519 --> 00:05:47,839
Yeah.

112
00:05:47,839 --> 00:05:50,199
The salary will increase. It definitely will.

113
00:05:51,160 --> 00:05:53,079
If the salary goes up...

114
00:05:53,079 --> 00:05:54,439
...the financial pressure won't be so heavy.

115
00:05:54,439 --> 00:05:55,199
Then Xiaoshi...

116
00:05:55,199 --> 00:05:56,800
...can be transferred back sooner, right?

117
00:05:56,800 --> 00:05:58,360
About whether she can come back or not...

118
00:05:58,360 --> 00:06:00,879
I... I'll wait until I'm officially in the position,

119
00:06:00,879 --> 00:06:02,079
then I'll discuss it properly with her.

120
00:06:02,079 --> 00:06:03,360
Don't worry about that for now.

121
00:06:05,000 --> 00:06:07,439
Don't be in such a rush about this.

122
00:06:08,040 --> 00:06:09,600
A promotion has its advantages,

123
00:06:09,600 --> 00:06:10,920
but it also comes with pressure.

124
00:06:11,199 --> 00:06:14,120
You just focus on doing a good job at work.

125
00:06:14,439 --> 00:06:15,920
From now on,

126
00:06:15,920 --> 00:06:18,360
our family's life will just get better and better.

127
00:06:18,360 --> 00:06:19,199
Right?

128
00:06:19,199 --> 00:06:19,560
Yes, Dad.

129
00:06:19,560 --> 00:06:20,199
Let me tell you,

130
00:06:20,199 --> 00:06:21,519
our family's good days are just beginning.

131
00:06:21,519 --> 00:06:21,920
As for you...

132
00:06:21,920 --> 00:06:23,519
...really, don't put so much pressure on yourself.

133
00:06:23,519 --> 00:06:24,879
Take your time with that script.

134
00:06:24,920 --> 00:06:25,360
Okay?

135
00:06:25,360 --> 00:06:25,839
Okay, okay, okay.

136
00:06:25,839 --> 00:06:26,920
Alright, I'll take it easy. I'll take it easy.

137
00:06:26,920 --> 00:06:28,319
Right, right, right.

138
00:06:28,319 --> 00:06:29,199
Qiu'er!

139
00:06:30,360 --> 00:06:30,800
You got promoted!

140
00:06:30,800 --> 00:06:31,360
Chunsheng.

141
00:06:31,360 --> 00:06:33,199
Promoted, promoted, promoted!

142
00:06:34,079 --> 00:06:34,759
Uncle, Auntie.

143
00:06:34,759 --> 00:06:36,040
Then we have to celebrate!

144
00:06:36,040 --> 00:06:37,439
Come to my place for some good food. Let's go.

145
00:06:37,439 --> 00:06:38,600
Let's all go together.

146
00:06:38,800 --> 00:06:40,879
No, no. You boys go ahead first.

147
00:06:40,879 --> 00:06:42,800
I still have some lines to work on.

148
00:06:43,079 --> 00:06:43,839
You go on ahead.

149
00:06:43,839 --> 00:06:45,759
Alright then, we won't stand on ceremony with you two.

150
00:06:45,759 --> 00:06:46,439
Let's go, let's go, Qiu'er.

151
00:06:46,439 --> 00:06:47,560
Let's go.

152
00:06:48,360 --> 00:06:49,519
Sorry about that.

153
00:06:49,519 --> 00:06:50,639
What good food do you want to eat?

154
00:06:50,639 --> 00:06:51,959
Hairy crabs!

155
00:06:53,439 --> 00:06:55,079
This is perfect now.

156
00:06:55,360 --> 00:06:56,199
Delicious.

157
00:06:57,399 --> 00:06:58,639
Let me propose a toast to everyone.

158
00:06:58,639 --> 00:07:01,199
Special thanks to all the leaders for attending my...

159
00:07:01,199 --> 00:07:02,360
...humble promotion celebration.

160
00:07:02,360 --> 00:07:03,879
This promotion banquet, right?

161
00:07:03,920 --> 00:07:06,920
Special thanks to Brother Wang, Brother Wang...

162
00:07:06,920 --> 00:07:08,839
No, Director Ma!

163
00:07:08,839 --> 00:07:10,079
Director Ma!

164
00:07:10,079 --> 00:07:11,879
Brother Ma, Brother Ma, my apologies, apologies.

165
00:07:12,439 --> 00:07:13,519
Pleasure, pleasure.

166
00:07:13,600 --> 00:07:15,560
Li, Li, Li... Sis Li, Li... Sis Li!

167
00:07:15,560 --> 00:07:17,160
Long live Sis Li! Sis Li!

168
00:07:17,160 --> 00:07:18,319
Coming, coming!

169
00:07:18,319 --> 00:07:19,600
Pleasure, pleasure.

170
00:07:19,600 --> 00:07:20,800
He's happy today.

171
00:07:20,839 --> 00:07:21,600
I'm telling you, don't...

172
00:07:21,600 --> 00:07:24,079
Don't drink it all. Don't drink anymore.

173
00:07:25,120 --> 00:07:26,759
Here, have some fruit.

174
00:07:26,759 --> 00:07:27,439
Come on, come on.

175
00:07:27,439 --> 00:07:28,920
Hurry, hurry, hurry up.

176
00:07:29,360 --> 00:07:30,519
Eat some fruit.

177
00:07:30,519 --> 00:07:31,199
Eat fruit.

178
00:07:31,439 --> 00:07:32,800
How did he get this drunk?

179
00:07:32,839 --> 00:07:33,759
A toast just for you. Just for you.

180
00:07:33,759 --> 00:07:34,079
Come on, come on.

181
00:07:34,079 --> 00:07:35,920
Isn't he just happy about the promotion?

182
00:07:36,120 --> 00:07:37,040
You, hurry up.

183
00:07:37,040 --> 00:07:37,800
Here, you take charge.

184
00:07:37,800 --> 00:07:38,360
He can't drink anymore.

185
00:07:38,360 --> 00:07:39,519
Yes, I know, I know, I know.

186
00:07:39,519 --> 00:07:41,199
Come on, come on. Let me toast everyone.

187
00:07:41,360 --> 00:07:42,160
Sis.

188
00:07:42,199 --> 00:07:43,519
Okay, thank you, Sis.

189
00:07:43,519 --> 00:07:44,519
Thank you all.

190
00:07:44,519 --> 00:07:44,920
Thanks.

191
00:07:44,920 --> 00:07:46,079
Enjoy the food and drinks.

192
00:07:46,079 --> 00:07:47,800
Please offer your valuable suggestions in the future.

193
00:07:47,800 --> 00:07:48,639
Right, more valuable suggestions.

194
00:07:48,639 --> 00:07:49,560
You're too kind.

195
00:07:49,560 --> 00:07:51,399
I'll finish mine. Everyone, drink at your own pace.

196
00:07:51,399 --> 00:07:51,759
Okay.

197
00:07:51,759 --> 00:07:52,120
Alright.

198
00:07:52,120 --> 00:07:52,759
Thank you.

199
00:07:55,160 --> 00:07:56,120
Alright.

200
00:07:56,120 --> 00:07:57,560
Come on, come on, let's dig in.

201
00:07:57,560 --> 00:07:58,399
Eat, eat, eat some fruit.

202
00:07:58,399 --> 00:07:59,759
Have some fruit. Have some fruit.

203
00:07:59,759 --> 00:08:00,800
Have some dishes.

204
00:08:01,160 --> 00:08:03,000
Should I go get some water?

205
00:08:03,000 --> 00:08:03,920
Go get some, go get some.

206
00:08:03,920 --> 00:08:05,000
Go get some water.

207
00:08:24,560 --> 00:08:25,160
What's wrong?

208
00:08:26,160 --> 00:08:27,759
You're really something, you know that?

209
00:08:28,319 --> 00:08:30,399
You were the one who told me not to meddle before.

210
00:08:30,399 --> 00:08:31,839
You were the one who left without a word.

211
00:08:32,000 --> 00:08:34,360
And now you're back, making a complete mess of things.

212
00:08:34,360 --> 00:08:35,519
What exactly do you want?

213
00:08:37,639 --> 00:08:40,159
You're still angry about the cafe thing?

214
00:08:40,840 --> 00:08:41,919
You've misunderstood.

215
00:08:42,440 --> 00:08:45,000
Feifei was worried you'd be tricked,

216
00:08:45,120 --> 00:08:46,120
so she asked me to check out...

217
00:08:46,120 --> 00:08:47,519
...that guy's character, that's all.

218
00:08:49,159 --> 00:08:50,159
Everyone in this whole alley...

219
00:08:50,159 --> 00:08:51,879
...combined doesn't have as many schemes as you do.

220
00:08:53,159 --> 00:08:54,320
Let me say this one more time.

221
00:08:54,320 --> 00:08:55,120
Matters of the heart...

222
00:08:55,120 --> 00:08:56,519
...if anyone's to meddle, it's not your turn.

223
00:08:56,519 --> 00:08:57,639
That's my uncle's job.

224
00:08:57,919 --> 00:08:59,759
And work matters are even less your business.

225
00:09:00,159 --> 00:09:01,559
You pulling Wang Fei into this...

226
00:09:01,559 --> 00:09:03,000
...I can let that slide.

227
00:09:03,320 --> 00:09:05,159
You fooled everyone with a fake medical report...

228
00:09:05,519 --> 00:09:06,840
...and I don't want to expose you either.

229
00:09:07,759 --> 00:09:08,120
In short,

230
00:09:08,120 --> 00:09:10,039
from now on, let's just leave each other alone, okay?

231
00:09:13,120 --> 00:09:14,159
You knew all along.

232
00:09:19,639 --> 00:09:20,840
After all that trouble...

233
00:09:21,120 --> 00:09:24,200
...you came back just to hold the exhibition and fulfill your wish, right?

234
00:09:24,320 --> 00:09:25,399
Why can he help you...

235
00:09:25,399 --> 00:09:26,399
...but I can't?

236
00:09:27,399 --> 00:09:28,559
He helps me, I help him.

237
00:09:28,559 --> 00:09:29,840
We're friends helping each other.

238
00:09:30,000 --> 00:09:32,000
And you? Why do you want to help me?

239
00:09:32,000 --> 00:09:32,759
Isn't it clear in your heart?

240
00:09:32,759 --> 00:09:33,240
I...

241
00:09:33,639 --> 00:09:34,799
You... you what?

242
00:09:36,639 --> 00:09:38,000
We're friends too, aren't we?

243
00:09:39,840 --> 00:09:40,840
I've said it before.

244
00:09:40,840 --> 00:09:42,000
You don't owe me anything.

245
00:09:49,639 --> 00:09:52,360
You know my situation very well.

246
00:09:53,080 --> 00:09:54,639
It's not that I don't want to do many things.

247
00:09:55,399 --> 00:09:56,480
It's that I can't.

248
00:09:58,159 --> 00:09:59,279
That so-called kind of...

249
00:10:00,399 --> 00:10:01,200
promise.

250
00:10:01,200 --> 00:10:03,120
Given my condition, I can't make one.

251
00:10:03,120 --> 00:10:04,639
Don't you get it yet?

252
00:10:05,320 --> 00:10:07,759
Yes, I confessed my feelings to you before.

253
00:10:07,759 --> 00:10:09,120
But when I said I liked you,

254
00:10:09,120 --> 00:10:10,559
I wasn't asking for anything in return.

255
00:10:10,559 --> 00:10:12,399
Because I thought you felt the same way I did.

256
00:10:13,000 --> 00:10:14,120
I thought if I said it out loud,

257
00:10:14,120 --> 00:10:15,120
you'd stop running away.

258
00:10:15,120 --> 00:10:16,159
You'd pull yourself together a bit.

259
00:10:16,159 --> 00:10:18,480
You'd find the courage to fight your illness.

260
00:10:19,320 --> 00:10:20,919
But I guess I was wrong.

261
00:10:21,639 --> 00:10:24,000
Because you're a complete coward.

262
00:10:25,200 --> 00:10:27,320
You don't have the courage to face your own feelings.

263
00:10:27,360 --> 00:10:29,639
Or the courage to face your own condition.

264
00:10:31,720 --> 00:10:32,759
I've thought about it too.

265
00:10:34,440 --> 00:10:35,440
I think someone like you...

266
00:10:35,440 --> 00:10:36,559
isn't worth my affection.

267
00:10:42,120 --> 00:10:44,000
If you interfere in my life again,

268
00:10:44,000 --> 00:10:45,879
I'll move out of the hutong immediately.

269
00:10:50,159 --> 00:10:51,000
You can leave now.

270
00:11:51,200 --> 00:11:51,879
Wang Chunsheng.

271
00:11:51,879 --> 00:11:53,159
What have you been doing all this time?

272
00:11:56,440 --> 00:11:57,159
What's this about?

273
00:11:57,159 --> 00:11:59,320
Got a date today? All dolled up.

274
00:12:02,000 --> 00:12:02,639
No.

275
00:12:03,200 --> 00:12:05,159
Isn't Teacher Xia Tian coming to collaborate?

276
00:12:05,279 --> 00:12:07,039
I gotta spruce myself up a bit.

277
00:12:07,519 --> 00:12:08,919
Hold on, hold on, hold on.

