00:25:07,759 --> 00:25:10,839
but around here, a man like your Big Brother...

555
00:25:11,319 --> 00:25:14,319
is absolutely top-notch.

556
00:25:14,440 --> 00:25:16,319
One in a hundred, a great guy.

557
00:25:19,519 --> 00:25:20,519
I think...

558
00:25:22,200 --> 00:25:24,000
You two should really have a good talk.

559
00:25:24,680 --> 00:25:26,599
Haven't you been lacking communication lately?

560
00:25:28,119 --> 00:25:29,000
Weiguo...

561
00:25:29,319 --> 00:25:32,759
What do you mean by "more communication"?

562
00:25:33,079 --> 00:25:35,240
Take me and your Big Brother, for example.

563
00:25:35,799 --> 00:25:37,200
We either talk about Feifei,

564
00:25:37,799 --> 00:25:40,799
or we talk about Penglexuan stuff.

565
00:25:41,319 --> 00:25:44,200
There's nothing else to talk about.

566
00:25:45,519 --> 00:25:46,759
Especially recently...

567
00:25:47,119 --> 00:25:49,759
He and Feifei are working on that...

568
00:25:49,880 --> 00:25:50,680
That thing of his...

569
00:25:50,680 --> 00:25:52,119
That... that account.

570
00:25:52,359 --> 00:25:53,119
I know.

571
00:25:55,400 --> 00:25:57,160
When they talk about it...

572
00:25:57,680 --> 00:25:59,559
I... I really can't understand it.

573
00:26:00,799 --> 00:26:01,799
And second...

574
00:26:01,799 --> 00:26:03,200
When I try to join in...

575
00:26:03,519 --> 00:26:05,000
I really can't get a word in.

576
00:26:06,759 --> 00:26:08,119
We're not like...

577
00:26:08,759 --> 00:26:10,000
Teacher Xiatian, right?

578
00:26:10,000 --> 00:26:11,000
She's...

579
00:26:11,000 --> 00:26:12,759
In the end, it's still about that Teacher Xiatian, isn't it?

580
00:26:12,759 --> 00:26:15,200
It's really not, nothing like that.

581
00:26:17,559 --> 00:26:18,759
How about this, Sis.

582
00:26:20,319 --> 00:26:22,200
I have an idea for you. Will you listen?

583
00:26:22,319 --> 00:26:23,400
What idea?

584
00:26:23,960 --> 00:26:26,640
You should go stay at your parents' place for a few days.

585
00:26:26,759 --> 00:26:28,119
Put aside things at home and the restaurant.

586
00:26:28,119 --> 00:26:29,079
Just let them be for now.

587
00:26:29,319 --> 00:26:31,720
No, no, both places need someone.

588
00:26:31,720 --> 00:26:32,920
Didn't you say...

589
00:26:33,400 --> 00:26:35,039
you never get a break all year?

590
00:26:35,240 --> 00:26:35,839
This time...

591
00:26:35,839 --> 00:26:38,119
just treat it as giving yourself a big vacation, okay?

592
00:26:40,759 --> 00:26:41,880
That wouldn't work, would it?

593
00:26:42,400 --> 00:26:44,000
What if something happens?

594
00:26:44,000 --> 00:26:45,039
Just give it a try.

595
00:26:46,000 --> 00:26:47,119
Nothing will happen.

596
00:26:49,400 --> 00:26:50,480
What could possibly happen?

597
00:26:52,920 --> 00:26:53,599
Alright.

598
00:26:56,480 --> 00:26:57,000
A big vacation.

599
00:26:57,000 --> 00:26:57,519
Okay.

600
00:26:57,839 --> 00:26:59,839
Relax, just rel...

601
00:27:24,240 --> 00:27:26,400
Jing'er, get me a pair of socks.

602
00:27:30,920 --> 00:27:33,119
Jing'er, get me a clean pair of socks.

603
00:27:39,519 --> 00:27:40,279
Jing'er?

604
00:27:43,400 --> 00:27:44,160
Jing'er?

605
00:27:46,519 --> 00:27:47,480
Where's your mom?

606
00:28:04,039 --> 00:28:05,160
Get me a bowl of congee.

607
00:28:10,759 --> 00:28:11,599
Jing'er?

608
00:28:12,000 --> 00:28:13,119
Dad, what's wrong?

609
00:28:13,119 --> 00:28:15,039
Old problem, it's fine.

610
00:28:15,279 --> 00:28:16,920
I'm helping my mom take care of him for a few days.

611
00:28:16,920 --> 00:28:18,720
Wait, should I come over to check?

612
00:28:19,000 --> 00:28:20,000
Don't bother.

613
00:28:20,000 --> 00:28:21,519
Aren't you swamped with things at the restaurant?

614
00:28:21,519 --> 00:28:22,759
I'll be back in a couple of days.

615
00:28:24,000 --> 00:28:26,039
Okay, then give my regards to Mom and Dad.

616
00:28:26,240 --> 00:28:28,640
Let me know if anything comes up.

617
00:28:35,720 --> 00:28:38,480
Dad, did Mom wash those new insoles for me?

618
00:28:38,480 --> 00:28:39,200
Have you seen them?

619
00:28:41,039 --> 00:28:42,759
Are they on the shoe rack?

620
00:28:43,119 --> 00:28:44,000
I looked, they're not there.

621
00:28:46,319 --> 00:28:47,799
Call your mom and ask.

622
00:28:48,160 --> 00:28:49,839
You didn't get the chopsticks.

623
00:28:52,400 --> 00:28:53,240
Hold on a sec.

624
00:29:06,079 --> 00:29:06,720
Boss.

625
00:29:07,039 --> 00:29:08,720
We're getting ready for customers.

626
00:29:11,599 --> 00:29:14,240
Bro, it's almost time for customers to arrive.

627
00:29:14,240 --> 00:29:15,720
Why isn't Sister Jing here yet?

628
00:29:15,720 --> 00:29:16,720
What are we supposed to do?

629
00:29:16,720 --> 00:29:19,200
No, your sister-in-law has some family matters.

630
00:29:19,200 --> 00:29:20,200
She went back to take care of it.

631
00:29:20,200 --> 00:29:22,599
Isn't the restaurant just these few things?

632
00:29:22,920 --> 00:29:24,960
Sister Jing usually handles everything.

633
00:29:24,960 --> 00:29:26,920
Without her, we have no backbone.

634
00:29:27,200 --> 00:29:28,720
Am I not here?

635
00:29:28,960 --> 00:29:29,720
Go on, get busy.

636
00:29:29,960 --> 00:29:30,559
Alright.

637
00:29:30,839 --> 00:29:32,440
Let's all pick up the pace then.

638
00:29:37,480 --> 00:29:38,160
Big Brother.

639
00:29:38,759 --> 00:29:39,720
What's up?

640
00:29:40,200 --> 00:29:41,240
What's wrong?

641
00:29:41,240 --> 00:29:43,359
No, you sit down here first.

642
00:29:45,960 --> 00:29:47,039
It's nothing, nothing.

643
00:29:47,200 --> 00:29:48,599
What's wrong? What's wrong?

644
00:29:48,799 --> 00:29:49,680
It's nothing, nothing, nothing.

645
00:29:49,680 --> 00:29:50,480
It's fine, it's fine.

646
00:29:50,480 --> 00:29:51,400
I accidentally broke it.

647
00:29:51,400 --> 00:29:52,440
I'll clean it up, it'll be fine.

648
00:29:52,720 --> 00:29:54,119
You scared me!

649
00:29:55,200 --> 00:29:56,200
Qiu'er, what's wrong?

650
00:29:56,880 --> 00:29:58,920
Weiguo, that financial product of yours...

651
00:29:58,920 --> 00:30:00,319
When do you estimate you'll buy it?

652
00:30:00,720 --> 00:30:02,200
There are still some procedures being processed.

653
00:30:02,200 --> 00:30:03,119
Soon, very soon.

654
00:30:03,440 --> 00:30:04,920
I haven't even become Assistant Branch Manager yet,

655
00:30:04,920 --> 00:30:05,680
and I already have a ton of tasks.

656
00:30:05,680 --> 00:30:06,680
I'm not trying to pressure you.

657
00:30:06,680 --> 00:30:08,039
When it's convenient, let's just...

658
00:30:08,400 --> 00:30:09,480
be a bit more swift.

659
00:30:10,720 --> 00:30:11,559
Okay, I got it.

660
00:30:14,720 --> 00:30:17,200
Lao Tong, the boss is looking for you again.

661
00:30:19,440 --> 00:30:20,720
The boss is looking for me again?

662
00:30:27,480 --> 00:30:28,160
Liu Xing

663
00:30:28,160 --> 00:30:30,519
Quick, quick, quick, have a seat.

664
00:30:33,640 --> 00:30:36,160
Although your approval isn't official yet,

665
00:30:36,160 --> 00:30:37,640
based on past practice,

666
00:30:37,640 --> 00:30:39,759
this is a done deal.

667
00:30:40,799 --> 00:30:42,920
So we need to get to work right now.

668
00:30:43,400 --> 00:30:44,519
This is the bank's newly set

669
00:30:44,519 --> 00:30:45,640
key performance indicators for next quarter.

670
00:30:45,640 --> 00:30:46,880
Here, take a look.

671
00:30:59,359 --> 00:31:02,480
How... how did it jump so much all at once?

672
00:31:02,640 --> 00:31:04,759
Doing business is like rowing upstream.

673
00:31:04,799 --> 00:31:06,279
If you don't advance, you fall behind.

674
00:31:07,839 --> 00:31:08,359
We...

675
00:31:08,640 --> 00:31:11,240
We didn't even meet last month's target.

676
00:31:12,119 --> 00:31:13,839
That's exactly why we're bringing you up.

677
00:31:14,359 --> 00:31:16,880
Otherwise, I'd just keep Xiao Jia, wouldn't I?

678
00:31:17,920 --> 00:31:19,720
You really should have kept Xiao Jia.

679
00:31:21,400 --> 00:31:22,400
No, it's just...

680
00:31:22,920 --> 00:31:25,799
Everyone's already under a lot of pressure.

681
00:31:26,000 --> 00:31:27,359
If you go by this,

682
00:31:27,359 --> 00:31:29,400
I'm afraid everyone will have complaints.

683
00:31:29,680 --> 00:31:31,920
Without pressure, a person is aimless.

684
00:31:32,039 --> 00:31:33,640
Pressure is also motivation.

685
00:31:34,160 --> 00:31:36,160
Lao Tong, you're capable.

686
00:31:36,160 --> 00:31:37,559
Motivate the team more.

687
00:31:39,480 --> 00:31:42,400
You... I really think this is a bit unrealistic.

688
00:31:42,400 --> 00:31:43,880
Look at how much it increased.

689
00:31:43,880 --> 00:31:45,240
I think this... this...

690
00:31:45,240 --> 00:31:47,160
This can't be done.

691
00:31:47,920 --> 00:31:51,119
Aren't you cozying up to Director Qiu now?

692
00:31:53,119 --> 00:31:55,400
Just keep going down that path.

693
00:31:56,759 --> 00:31:58,599
That circle of close friends around her,

694
00:31:58,640 --> 00:32:00,400
how you won over Director Qiu,

695
00:32:00,519 --> 00:32:02,480
just keep doing that to win them over.

696
00:32:03,160 --> 00:32:04,400
You really think highly of me.

697
00:32:04,400 --> 00:32:05,920
Win over her circle of friends?

698
00:32:05,920 --> 00:32:07,119
The whole group... it's a total wipeout.

699
00:32:07,119 --> 00:32:09,359
Understood, got it.

700
00:32:12,279 --> 00:32:13,599
And that wealthy relative of yours,

701
00:32:14,039 --> 00:32:15,119
hurry them along.

702
00:32:15,119 --> 00:32:16,799
Don't just make noise without action.

703
00:32:21,039 --> 00:32:23,119
If you heard what I said, then you understand.

704
00:32:33,400 --> 00:32:35,359
Lao Tong, why are the targets increased again?

705
00:32:35,359 --> 00:32:36,640
It's simply impossible to meet.

706
00:32:36,640 --> 00:32:37,400
Yes, yes, yes.

707
00:32:37,400 --> 00:32:40,200
Brother Tong, I'm just not doing it anymore.

708
00:32:40,400 --> 00:32:42,799
Look at me, I'm all messed up.

709
00:32:42,920 --> 00:32:44,039
All messed up.

710
00:32:44,160 --> 00:32:46,880
Brother Tong, how did you talk to the Vice President?

711
00:32:46,880 --> 00:32:48,640
It's clearly impossible, isn't it?

712
00:32:48,880 --> 00:32:50,119
Yes, yes, yes.

713
00:32:50,240 --> 00:32:52,160
Right, last month's performance targets,

714
00:32:52,160 --> 00:32:53,920
How are you talking to Brother Tong?

715
00:32:53,920 --> 00:32:55,640
Aren't you just adding pressure for him?

716
00:32:56,119 --> 00:32:57,400
Brother Tong definitely has a plan.

717
00:32:57,400 --> 00:32:59,480
Anyway, I haven't paid this month's rent yet.

718
00:32:59,480 --> 00:33:00,160
Right, right, right.

719
00:33:00,480 --> 00:33:02,400
No, hey, hey, everyone, don't panic.

720
00:33:02,400 --> 00:33:04,400
I... I understand all your concerns.

721
00:33:04,400 --> 00:33:05,680
I... I'm also trying to figure something out.

722
00:33:05,920 --> 00:33:07,039
I'm trying to figure something out too.

723
00:33:19,559 --> 00:33:20,680
What's going on here?

724
00:33:20,880 --> 00:33:22,160
I ordered the sauteed lamb in sauce.

725
00:33:22,160 --> 00:33:23,160
What did you bring me?

726
00:33:23,319 --> 00:33:24,240
Scallion lamb stir-fry.

727
00:33:24,240 --> 00:33:25,400
How many times have I told you?

728
00:33:25,400 --> 00:33:26,400
I don't eat scallions. I don't eat scallions!

729
00:33:26,400 --> 00:33:27,440
Why can't you remember?

730
00:33:27,519 --> 00:33:28,640
So sorry, sir.

731
00:33:28,640 --> 00:33:30,640
We must have mixed up your order.

732
00:33:30,640 --> 00:33:32,119
I'll change it for you right now.

733
00:33:32,160 --> 00:33:34,400
And I'll give you half a Peking duck on the house.

734
00:33:34,400 --> 00:33:35,160
How does that sound?

735
00:33:35,160 --> 00:33:36,240
Please, calm down.

736
00:33:36,240 --> 00:33:37,400
That's more like it.

737
00:33:37,799 --> 00:33:39,920
Alright, hurry up and change it for him. Quick.

738
00:33:40,359 --> 00:33:40,920
Okay.

739
00:33:41,400 --> 00:33:43,920
Hurry, and don't mess it up this time.

740
00:33:47,680 --> 00:33:48,559
Xiao Zhang.

741
00:33:49,599 --> 00:33:50,920
What payment?

742
00:33:52,400 --> 00:33:53,279
Thank you, thank you.

743
00:33:53,279 --> 00:33:54,519
Come again, come again!

744
00:33:55,519 --> 00:33:56,400
Take care.

745
00:33:57,160 --> 00:33:57,920
Wait, these matters...

746
00:33:57,920 --> 00:33:59,279
Doesn't your sister-in-law usually

747
00:33:59,279 --> 00:34:00,559
handle the contact for those?

748
00:34:01,240 --> 00:34:02,160
No, don't worry.

749
00:34:02,160 --> 00:34:03,559
We won't shortchange you.

750
00:34:03,559 --> 00:34:04,119
Here's what you do.

751
00:34:04,119 --> 00:34:05,400
Send me that invoice.

752
00:34:05,400 --> 00:34:06,440
I'll transfer you the money now.

753
00:34:06,680 --> 00:34:08,000
No problem, no problem.

754
00:34:08,639 --> 00:34:09,159
Alright then.

755
00:34:09,880 --> 00:34:11,639
Does it really take this long to settle a bill?

756
00:34:11,639 --> 00:34:13,119
Sorry, sorry, just a moment, please.

757
00:34:13,559 --> 00:34:15,039
Such a big restaurant,

758
00:34:15,239 --> 00:34:16,880
and you can't even issue a receipt?

759
00:34:16,920 --> 00:34:17,679
Let me tell you something.

760
00:34:17,679 --> 00:34:18,920
Don't give me excuses.

761
00:34:19,000 --> 00:34:20,639
If you don't give me a receipt,

762
00:34:20,639 --> 00:34:22,639
I'll call and report you right now.

763
00:34:22,920 --> 00:34:24,159
No, no, no, miss.

764
00:34:24,159 --> 00:34:25,119
Wh-what's going on?

765
00:34:25,320 --> 00:34:26,679
We're out of receipts, boss.

766
00:34:26,679 --> 00:34:28,400
Sister Jing usually applies for them.

767
00:34:28,400 --> 00:34:29,559
I don't know how.

768
00:34:30,639 --> 00:34:32,239
Miss, I'm so sorry.

769
00:34:32,239 --> 00:34:34,119
We're having a bit of a situation at the shop today.

770
00:34:34,159 --> 00:34:35,639
How about this?

771
00:34:35,639 --> 00:34:37,400
Get a piece of paper and a pen.

772
00:34:37,400 --> 00:34:39,239
Could you write down your company name

773
00:34:39,400 --> 00:34:41,440
and your mailing address for me?

774
00:34:41,440 --> 00:34:42,920
I'll mail it to you by express.

775
00:34:42,920 --> 00:34:44,320
And then, for this bill,

776
00:34:44,400 --> 00:34:46,679
I'll give you a twenty percent discount, okay?

777
00:34:46,920 --> 00:34:48,400
Quick, get her a drink.

778
00:34:48,400 --> 00:34:48,920
Alright.

779
00:34:48,920 --> 00:34:49,639
Get an expensive one.

780
00:34:49,639 --> 00:34:50,400
Thank you, miss.

781
00:34:50,400 --> 00:34:51,920
Come again, come again!

782
00:34:52,920 --> 00:34:53,440
Master.

783
00:34:53,440 --> 00:34:53,920
What's up?

784
00:34:53,920 --> 00:34:55,400
Why haven't we gotten paid yet?

785
00:34:55,639 --> 00:34:57,119
Wasn't it supposed to be yesterday?

786
00:34:57,400 --> 00:34:58,239
Yeah.

787
00:34:58,400 --> 00:35:00,679
Usually, the mistress sends it out first thing.

788
00:35:01,119 --> 00:35:02,320
You know my family situation.

789
00:35:02,320 --> 00:35:02,880
Thank you, thank you.

790
00:35:02,880 --> 00:35:03,280
I really need the money.

791
00:35:03,280 --> 00:35:03,800
Sorry about this.

792
00:35:03,800 --> 00:35:05,280
Right, it hasn't been sent, has it?

793
00:35:05,400 --> 00:35:06,320
Here's what you do, I, I, I...

794
00:35:06,320 --> 00:35:07,920
I'll... I'll transfer it to you right now.

795
00:35:07,920 --> 00:35:09,000
Later, have your sister-in-law

796
00:35:09,000 --> 00:35:10,119
handle the formal transfer for you, okay?

797
00:35:10,119 --> 00:35:11,199
Thanks, Master. I'll go serve the duck now.

798
00:35:11,199 --> 00:35:11,599
Alright, alright.

799
00:35:11,599 --> 00:35:13,119
Go on, get back to work.

800
00:35:18,199 --> 00:35:19,239
Where's my duck?

801
00:35:19,239 --> 00:35:19,960
Sorry.

802
00:35:21,079 --> 00:35:22,559
What are you doing here causing trouble?

803
00:35:22,559 --> 00:35:24,199
Go back home and rest.

804
00:35:24,199 --> 00:35:24,679
Go on, get out of here.

805
00:35:24,679 --> 00:35:26,440
A bit lost without your wife around, huh?

806
00:35:26,440 --> 00:35:27,280
Can't handle it all, can you?

807
00:35:27,480 --> 00:35:29,800
It's okay. Just busy for a bit, that's all.

808
00:35:29,800 --> 00:35:30,760
Waiter!

809
00:35:30,960 --> 00:35:31,679
Coming!

810
00:35:31,800 --> 00:35:33,400
When's my roast duck coming?

811
00:35:33,400 --> 00:35:34,119
I've been waiting forever.

812
00:35:34,119 --> 00:35:35,880
Alright, I'll hurry them up for you.

813
00:35:36,280 --> 00:35:37,960
What about that customer's roast duck?

814
00:35:38,440 --> 00:35:39,119
What's up?

815
00:35:39,880 --> 00:35:41,039
Come here, let's talk.

816
00:35:45,719 --> 00:35:46,800
Come on, sit, sit.

817
00:35:56,239 --> 00:35:57,920
So, what did you want to talk about?

818
00:36:00,079 --> 00:36:01,199
Ma Weiguo.

819
00:36:01,519 --> 00:36:03,199
You're lying to us again, aren't you?

820
00:36:03,880 --> 00:36:06,199
When will you ever tell the truth?

821
00:36:07,960 --> 00:36:09,840
Brother Bao, that thing you asked me to check,

822
00:36:09,840 --> 00:36:11,559
about the Harvard Cancer Research Center...

823
00:36:11,559 --> 00:36:12,719
I've looked into it.

824
00:36:12,800 --> 00:36:14,280
They don't have any

825
00:36:14,280 --> 00:36:16,079
new technology for glioblastoma.

826
00:36:16,280 --> 00:36:17,280
How can that be?

827
00:36:17,480 --> 00:36:18,599
Are you sure you didn't make a mistake?

828
00:36:19,360 --> 00:36:21,280
The person I asked was Mike,

829
00:36:21,280 --> 00:36:22,559
Professor Zhou's assistant.

830
00:36:22,559 --> 00:36:23,559
This guy even said,

831
00:36:23,559 --> 00:36:25,719
if this new tech gets developed,

832
00:36:25,719 --> 00:36:27,320
next year's Nobel Prize in Medicine

833
00:36:27,320 --> 00:36:28,760
is a sure thing.

834
00:36:30,079 --> 00:36:31,039
Ma Weiguo!

835
00:36:33,679 --> 00:36:35,719
Ma Weiguo, get out here!

836
00:36:36,159 --> 00:36:36,920
Uncle.

837
00:36:38,360 --> 00:36:39,880
What did he do to upset you this time?

838
00:36:40,199 --> 00:36:42,199
This jerk lied to us again.

839
00:36:42,719 --> 00:36:45,360
You mean the Harvard Cancer Research Center,

840
00:36:45,360 --> 00:36:46,320
the new technology thing, right?

841
00:36:46,320 --> 00:36:48,960
What new technology? It's all fake.

842
00:36:50,920 --> 00:36:52,159
You knew all along?

843
00:36:53,760 --> 00:36:55,360
I know a fair bit about his condition.

844
00:36:55,360 --> 00:36:56,599
A quick check showed it was fake.

845
00:36:56,679 --> 00:36:58,440
Then why didn't you tell me sooner?

846
00:36:59,360 --> 00:37:02,000
I was afraid you'd get worried again if I told you.

847
00:37:02,480 --> 00:37:03,800
How can I not worry?

848
00:37:04,199 --> 00:37:05,679
We all care about him so much,

849
00:37:05,679 --> 00:37:06,360
and what does he do?

850
00:37:06,360 --> 00:37:07,800
Hires an actor to fool us.

851
00:37:07,960 --> 00:37:09,199
What was he thinking?

852
00:37:09,440 --> 00:37:10,519
If he has the energy for that,

853
00:37:10,519 --> 00:37:11,760
why doesn't he focus on getting better?

854
00:37:12,159 --> 00:37:14,320
I know, I thought the same way at first.

855
00:37:14,920 --> 00:37:16,519
But after this time,

856
00:37:16,719 --> 00:37:18,239
let's not worry on his behalf.

857
00:37:20,440 --> 00:37:21,800
There's a patient support group.

858
00:37:21,800 --> 00:37:24,559
I learned about his situation in there.

859
00:37:24,760 --> 00:37:26,719
His case isn't that unusual.

860
00:37:26,800 --> 00:37:29,079
Some people don't want to burden their families.

861
00:37:29,079 --> 00:37:31,119
Some are just angry with themselves.

862
00:37:31,119 --> 00:37:32,840
And others just want to let things run their course

863
00:37:32,840 --> 00:37:34,079
until the end of their lives.

864
00:37:35,440 --> 00:37:38,559
I think the illness is his own.

865
00:37:38,960 --> 00:37:40,519
Our worrying for him is useless.

866
00:37:40,519 --> 00:37:42,039
It just makes everyone feel bad in the end,

867
00:37:42,079 --> 00:37:43,960
and puts a lot of pressure on him.

868
00:37:44,920 --> 00:37:46,039
So I think...

869
00:37:47,480 --> 00:37:49,599
I think we should respect his choice.

870
00:37:54,239 --> 00:37:55,199
She really

871
00:37:55,639 --> 00:37:56,719
said that to you?

872
00:37:57,039 --> 00:37:58,719
She sees things clearer than you do.

873
00:38:02,039 --> 00:38:03,320
I didn't want to lie to you all either.

874
00:38:03,599 --> 00:38:04,119
I just...

875
00:38:04,119 --> 00:38:04,840
Alright, alright.

876
00:38:05,360 --> 00:38:06,679
Don't say another word.

877
00:38:07,320 --> 00:38:08,760
I'll just pretend I know nothing.

878
00:38:09,199 --> 00:38:09,880
Lian Bao.

879
00:38:10,199 --> 00:38:11,480
If I were you,

880
00:38:11,639 --> 00:38:13,280
I'd find a way to live.

881
00:38:13,960 --> 00:38:15,440
Even if there's only the tiniest bit of hope,

882
00:38:15,440 --> 00:38:16,480
I wouldn't give up.

883
00:38:16,719 --> 00:38:18,679
But I'm not you.

884
00:38:21,320 --> 00:38:22,119
Right.

885
00:38:22,920 --> 00:38:24,679
No one can make decisions for someone else.

886
00:38:25,159 --> 00:38:26,719
Not even with good intentions.

887
00:38:27,960 --> 00:38:29,159
So I don't agree with you.

888
00:38:29,440 --> 00:38:30,639
But I respect you.

889
00:38:56,280 --> 00:38:57,400
Jing'er.

890
00:39:00,400 --> 00:39:02,719
Feifei, where's the toilet paper?

891
00:39:04,079 --> 00:39:05,079
Let me look.

892
00:39:05,079 --> 00:39:07,000
Hey, you used up the paper

893
00:39:07,000 --> 00:39:08,159
and didn't put in a new roll?

894
00:39:10,239 --> 00:39:11,679
Mom usually changes it.

895
00:39:11,679 --> 00:39:13,159
I don't know where it is.

896
00:39:15,400 --> 00:39:16,480
There isn't any.

897
00:39:18,960 --> 00:39:19,400
Come on.

898
00:39:19,400 --> 00:39:21,440
Then bring me some of the tissues from outside.

899
00:39:22,199 --> 00:39:23,400
Tissues?

900
00:39:23,559 --> 00:39:24,920
The tissues are gone too.

901
00:39:27,599 --> 00:39:29,719
Then find me an old test paper.

902
00:39:32,079 --> 00:39:33,360
Why is the power out?

903
00:39:33,480 --> 00:39:35,079
Yeah, why's the power out?

904
00:39:35,400 --> 00:39:37,360
Hey, hurry up and buy some electricity with your phone.

905
00:39:37,679 --> 00:39:38,400
Okay.

906
00:39:41,360 --> 00:39:41,960
Dad.

907
00:39:42,239 --> 00:39:44,639
To buy electricity, you need to enter the user number.

908
00:39:44,639 --> 00:39:46,320
Is it ten digits or thirteen?

909
00:39:46,320 --> 00:39:47,159
Do you remember?

910
00:39:47,480 --> 00:39:49,639
How would I remember? Your mom always does it.

911
00:39:49,639 --> 00:39:51,360
Call your mom and ask.

912
00:39:54,159 --> 00:39:55,760
I can't even stand up right now.

913
00:39:56,639 --> 00:39:58,559
Ask your mom when she's coming back.

914
00:40:00,159 --> 00:40:00,760
Okay.

915
00:40:01,719 --> 00:40:02,800
I heard you.

916
00:40:03,639 --> 00:40:06,400
Mom, how... how many more days are you staying out?

917
00:40:09,119 --> 00:40:11,360
She says she needs to stay a few more days.

918
00:40:14,719 --> 00:40:16,599
Get me an old test paper.

919
00:40:17,440 --> 00:40:18,719
My old test papers...

920
00:40:19,360 --> 00:40:20,920
I haven't finished checking the answers yet.

921
00:40:21,639 --> 00:40:22,480
Fine.

922
00:40:37,960 --> 00:40:38,880
Feifei.

923
00:40:40,159 --> 00:40:41,599
Have you seen my razor?

924
00:40:41,599 --> 00:40:42,559
Nope.

925
00:40:42,559 --> 00:40:44,079
Have you seen my headphones?

926
00:40:44,239 --> 00:40:45,199
Nope.

927
00:40:51,280 --> 00:40:52,199
Check the clothes.

928
00:41:10,400 --> 00:41:12,079
I was using them just yesterday.

929
00:41:30,760 --> 00:41:32,159
Found them!

930
00:41:32,159 --> 00:41:34,159
Hey, where do you think you're going?

931
00:41:36,760 --> 00:41:37,920
Did you find them?

932
00:41:38,039 --> 00:41:39,719
Not yet. I'm digging through this basket.

933
00:41:40,159 --> 00:41:41,559
Were they expensive, those headphones?

934
00:41:42,239 --> 00:41:43,119
Pretty expensive.

935
00:41:44,559 --> 00:41:46,360
I was listening to them yesterday.

936
00:41:47,920 --> 00:41:48,880
Wait, yesterday...

937
00:41:48,880 --> 00:41:50,199
you were wearing these pants, right?

938
00:41:50,400 --> 00:41:52,039
Yeah, weren't they washed?

939
00:41:53,880 --> 00:41:55,119
Darn it, darn it, darn it!

940
00:41:56,920 --> 00:41:58,239
You forgot to check the pockets!

941
00:41:59,079 --> 00:42:01,239
I haven't done laundry in over ten years!

942
00:42:07,400 --> 00:42:09,559
Try... try if they still... still work.

943
00:42:09,920 --> 00:42:10,400
No, no, no.

944
00:42:10,400 --> 00:42:11,400
This is bad, really bad.

945
00:42:11,400 --> 00:42:12,960
Don't turn them on yet. Don't plug them in.

946
00:42:12,960 --> 00:42:13,679
Uh, you know what?

947
00:42:13,679 --> 00:42:15,159
First, dry them with a hairdryer.

948
00:42:15,159 --> 00:42:15,599
Okay.

949
00:42:15,840 --> 00:42:16,760
Dry them first.
